'''Catió''' is a city in south eastern [[Guinea-Bissau]]. It is the capital of [[Tombali Region]].
Population 9,217 (2008 est).<ref>[http://world-gazetteer.com/wg.php?x=&men=gcis&lng=en&des=wg&srt=npan&col=abcdefghinoq&msz=1500&geo=-95 World Gazetteer] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081005204614/http://world-gazetteer.com/wg.php?x=&men=gcis&lng=en&des=wg&srt=npan&col=abcdefghinoq&msz=1500&geo=-95 |date=October 5, 2008 }}, Retrieved on June 16, 2008</ref>
Catio, along with [[Canjadude]] and other camps were besieged by the Portuguese in 1973.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=chQFAQAAIAAJ&q=Canjadude&dq=Canjadude&hl=en&ei=5uv_TMnUCseKhQen4dHPCw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5&ved=0CDsQ6AEwBA|title=Translations on Sub-Saharan Africa, Issues 1390-1397|publisher=United States. Joint Publications Research Service|year=1973|page=29}}</ref>
